>Without jumping too quickly to the metaphysics (or "stampeding to the
>clitoris" if you will) let me just say that I see T's long takes as, among
>other things, his appreciation of documentary --- and Theater. Capturing
>the life of a performance in a fiction film is the next best thing to
>capturing a real event. A real interaction of camera, characters as well as
>the inanimate world. An orchestration of chance and rehearsal. Tarkovsky
>had an affinity for American jazz and this is a similar interest, I think.
>He's been accused of working slow, taking a long time rehearsing
>complicated setup require even more time to take measures not to kill
>spontaneity in the performances. 
