Hi Everyone!  I'm still alive but real busy.  Just had a couple of things to say:

First, I agree with this guy to a point.  I love the camerawork in DM and think it DOES owe a lot to AT, but Jim is too much of a goofball, I think, to sustain the mystique necessary for the time-distortion AT pulls off.  Don't get me wrong, Jim is MY MAN, very much so, but I think it'd be interesting to see him really try to pull off the pacing which his wit sometimes won't allow.  (wow, I guess I could keep backpedalling on that one, but it's a valid point, I guess)  Incidentally, I think JJ's TIGUERO is awesome as well, and attacks this question from a different standpoint.  He (Jim) and film director Sam Fuller go to a remote land inhabited by primitive peoples Sam had filmed 30 years previous.  The crux of the film lies in showing these people, who continue a primitive existence, the images of themselves (minus 30 yrs.) and their reactions.  Very thought-provoking.


Also, has anyone ordered the Tark/Artmeyev CD's from Forced Exposure???  Reviews?  Just in case you missed it, FE's website is: 

http://www.fe.org/

...and they allegedly are distributing a reissue of the Artmeyev CD's from that Japanese label that reissued them a little while back... um..  not very helpful am I?  But check the website under Andrei Tarkovsky and they'll come up.. 
Take care everybody!

 
