NTSC stands for National Television Standards Committee,
or if you please Never Twice the Same Color. 

NTSC is the first and oldest commercial TV Color Standard, and being 
such, it incorporates a lot of compromises, which technically considered 
to be drawbacks, as opposed to the European standards, which were 
developed later in early 60's. PAL used in most of Western Europe, and 
SECAM, developed in France is still in use there as well as in 
ex-communist countries and in some Middle East countries. PAL and SECAM 
are partly compatible, resulting in Black and White playback of PAL 
videosignals on SECAM sets and vice versa. However those systems are not 
compatible with the NTSC standard.
By the way there is nothing illegal in converting PAL to NTSC, as such.
Anyway most of Kieslowsky is available in the States .
Just check with www.amazon.com, www.kencranes.com, www.reelcom.com among 
the others

