No you didn't choose the wrong word, I think your English is very good.
I was simply trying to make a joke. I thought it was very funny! The
idea that Tarkovsky is hypnotizing people into being fascists had me
laughing all day. I had this image in my head of a stern Tarkovsky
standing in between Tesla coils, arms outstretched.... 


And I did think you had an interesting point. But fascism is another
very complex subject. Have you read Susan Sontag's essay "Fascinating
Fascism"? In it she suggests that certain artistic expressions are
indicative of fascism: Art Deco, the Symbolists, she even mentions a
few films <italic>Fantasia</italic>, Kubrick's <italic>2001</italic>. I
see what she's talking about , though I don't agree with her
conclusion.


I've often wondered what she would say about Tarkovsky's aesthetics.


