John, you write:

<< Has anyone seen the film of Ulysses? UK version from mid sixties. I think
 directed by Joseph, or Joe Strick (?).
 
 It was clever, but I think only in reference to the book rather than as a
 film on its own. 
 
 Sometimes, what is latent in a novel needs to be spelled out in film and
 vice versa. >>

Yes, I saw it in a class once and then again on my own. Pretty bad, though
there were some clever moments, I agree. More than anything I thought it just
dated badly. It seemed like an old episode of the Avengers or something.
Strick isn't much of a director. I think, too, that there is a mistaken
attempt on the part of people filming Joyce to become artsy--Joyce was a
realist in the most ambitious sense of the word. All of his experiments were
aimed at portraying reality more effectively. 

Seamus  

