The general breakdown as regards opinions of Tarkovsky's work that I've seen
is this: half the viewers seem to prefer his earlier work (through Solaris),
less than half (but a more vocal bunch) prefer his later work but appreciate
his earlier work. And then a small amount like both more or less equally.

I fall into the second category: Rublev, Solaris, Ivan--all seem to me
interesting and at times brilliant. But it is Nostalghia and The Sacrifice
that keep me obsessed. Stalker and Mirror are in at a close second. The later
works seem more mature to me, more developed, and more focused--more poetic.
The earlier works seem to be exploring  ideas, but in a less developed and
less focused way.

Mind you: I feel that all of his films are exceptional--but I tend to see his
films as becoming more mature over time. This is not an especially thorough
argument on my part--but it should help get the ball rolling.

Seamus 

