In a message dated 98-08-31 05:52:23 EDT, you write:

<< , it seems not only rock stars get this kind of
 treatment by their fun clubs and groupies but also 'intellectuals' that
admire the
 'difficult' work of Tarkovsky etc. fall into the trap... because simply
education
 is not enough to have some marrow inside..... >>

I admit it, I'm a shameless groupie.  Also an intellectual, by default, the
things I like are the things intellectuals flock toward, though I own very
little black clothing and have no opinion whatsoever on Kierkegaard...  I'm
not sure about the education remark -- what kinds of assumptions can you
safely make?  As it happens I barely graduated from highschool and flunked out
of college almost instantly, but I assure you that no school would knock the
marrow out of me.

<< And again this reference to David Lynch; is he really the most intellectual
 director the west can show for itself now as an 'answer' to Tarkovsky? >>

Who ever claimed Lynch was an intellectual?  He's the great glorifier of the
small world and small ambitions of the anti-intellectual middle class, wholly
white, suburban, and frenziedly neurotic.  No point comparing him to
Tarkovsky, their work is utterly unrelated, it's like comparing William Blake
and Dennis Cooper.  But hey, sometimes I feel like being frenzied.
 
<< So like a game which band or rock star do you think would be comparable to
Andrei?>>

Tony always brings up Nick Drake, which makes sense:  his music is beautiful,
painful, spirtual, hopeful, and sometimes depressing if that's the way you
want to take it.

 <<ps. so color is 'commercial'? ..... great , now we get the puritan attitude
around
 here!!!! >>

Man, did you even read what I wrote??  Was I being cryptic or something?
Lighten up!

