Scott:

<< "words ,
 words, words ...If only I could DO something." >>

It is interesting that Alexander says this . . . and AFTER he has said "In the
beginning was the word. . ."  The rest of that quote from John, of course, is
"and the word was God." The word goes from a position of divinity to a
position of triviality (words words words.). This hints, I suppose, at the
path that Little Man will follow. He may quote John in the end . . . but like
his father he will probably move to "words words words"--and perhaps also to
renouncing words altogether.

I agree with what you say about The Sacrifice and dreaming--though I would
again argue that Nostalghia is linked to the Sacrifice in this way as well.
Nostalghia lapses into and out of dreams almost constantly.

Seamus

