Dear Friends,

I am intrigued by the verbal flings happening in our list and the only
thing which comes to my mind is the story of Babel.
Are we so helpless?

In this era of our existence, LIVING IS COMMUNICATION. Unless there is a
dialogue how can we communicate? If one decides unilaterally to end a
process of dialogue, is that helpful?

Isn't it necessary to consider, the concerned artist's expressed views on
why he create an object of art? Coming to opinions and methods of reading a
work of art, the primary thing we should always remember is that we are
speaking of a work of art, which is witnessed by us by our own uniquely
different ways.SO a Rose is NOT a Rose.

It is said that when Valmiki presented the great Indian Epic,"Ramayana"
he said," If thousand people read "Ramayana", then there will be
thousand new Ramayanas created." More so in Cinema. 

When we are discussing a work of art to understand it, we should have the
courage to see it from different angles and also not to overdo it beyond
its own intentions and definitions.

Then, why art? What are the functions of artists and philosophers in the
society? May be they create an "omnivalance" so that a dialogue occurs, and
through this dialogue a new meaning emerges, and through this new meaning,
a new reality is born![Hopefully a new reality for the better. Not another
Hiroshima]

We need not be afraid of words. After all we are created from word.

Let me quote Tarkovsky Himself now.

" Moreover, the great function of art is communication, since mutual
understanding is a force to unite people, and the spirit of communion is
one of the most important aspects of artistic creativity "

" In the end everything can be reduced to the one simple element, which is
all a person, can count upon in his existence: The capacity to Love.
That element can grow within the soul to become the supreme factor which
determines the meaning of a person's life. My function is to make whoever
sees my films aware of his need to love and to give his love, and aware
that beauty is summoning him."

I am afraid that, if Tarkovsky knows what is happening in our list -
prejudices and intolerance- he will not be all that happy.

Let cinema and discussions on cinema be an instrument of, understanding and
love, as Tarkovsky wished.

Long live CINEMA.

Sunny Joseph ISC.

