Listmaster:
	Is there someway we can overhaul the process by which people get on the list?  The web page with the form for subscribing is nice and convenient, but it doesn't force folks through the process of subscribing, which teaches one how to unsubscribe, right?  I left for labor Day, and came back with 1/3 of my email being 'take me off this shit' etc. :(  I love this list and read through it at work, but repeated similar emails draw attention from our web guy! ;)  The list is a blast, though, and I'm glad to be on it!

	So..  In this paper that I have sent a few of you, I discuss pacing a bit, and relate it to pacing in music.  I go through a few brief examples where there is great activity in the midst of relative calm (eg first half of sacrifice up to the flyover/pitcher crash) and bring up the question of manipulation of time by the composer/filmmaker.  He conscious accelerates the pace in a unique way via this graceful shifting, without resorting to a regular , steady, more active pace.  Thoughts?


