In a message dated 98-09-11 14:14:35 EDT, you write:

<< Some people understood it coud be a kind of action of the 
 ocean,that was reading Kris' deep thoughts.
  >>

This has always fascinated me:  the story of men using technology to acquire
information, but finding nothing is revealed about the subject, only about
their private agendas.  I'm ashamed to admit I don't recall the scene in
question, I'll go back to it.  This point is what the whole film hinges on for
me:  the way external quests lead one always back home, to the self, to the
unadmitted guilt, the suppressed pain.  As mystical as Tark can get, he's
really tangled up in the psyche, very complex, which can also mean
"unenlightened" (cf. Rob't John "Transformation" -- 3 types of consciousness
-- simple, complex [aka neurotic], and enlightened).  I hope I don't get
struck by lightning...
