Great discussion of Ozu.  I loved Autumn Sonata.  I'm just finished
editing my own personal "best of" Tarkovsky discussion from the
high-energy spring of 98 to distribute to friends.  For me it is a great
moment of found art/criticism.  Perhaps we could have an autumn edition?

I must tell you, I no longer collect entries.  Is anybody doing that? 
I'm too busy now and I'm tired.  However, I would like to publish that
incredible spring rush in some form someday.  It may be impossible due to
copywrite difficulties.

I tried showing Nostalghia to a well-educated (loves Cocteau's Beauty and
the Beast and Orpheus and Antonnioni's La'Ventura and Fellinni's La
Strada) art friend the other day.  She found it heavy-handed,
self-serving and so intrusively autobiographical that it interferred with
her willing suspension of disbelief.  

It is so rare that anybody says anything negative about Tarkovsky (on
this list) that I just thought I'd share it.

Thomas Beltzer

