Thomas!

Welcome back, mon frere! I have been, somewhat pathetically, waxing
nostalg(h)ic (pun intended) about that splendid renaissance we had early in
'98 for weeks now. The list is in somewhat wanting shape right now, though
Scott has been his good old formidable self--keeping the list alive almost
single-handedly. 

I can't tell you how glad I am to see you back. With you and Scott both
posting again and with some of the new additions we've had in the last few
weeks, I think an autumn rebirth is a distinct possibility (if seemingly
unnatural).

I'm glad, too, that you saw Autumn Afternoon. 

I'm not sure if anyone is collecting the posts of the last few months--I have
been relentlessly deleting almost everything in my archives, Tark or not.
Perhaps you could send me your personal collections as a text file? 

I mentioned your idea that the wife (etc.) in Solaris were, essentially,
icons--perhaps you could explain the idea more fully as you know that film
much better than I do, and have the Orthodox perspective as well.

I feel suddenly compelled to say marvelous sweeping things, but find that I am
uninspired. 

Let me be the first to welcome you back!

Seamus  
