Well, I didn't mean to insult you, so your reaction is a bit exaggerated.
Let me explain what I meant: Platonic ideal is something quite definite. For
example, take the notion of triangle. All the possible (or "physical")
triangles in the world have something in common, which is their "trianglity"
if I may say so. THIS is the ideal of triangle, more or less. Now if you
take this notion and use it on people you obviously should be careful. There
