Haim, you write:

<< Seamus, I admit that I should be more specific; actually I didn't object
 your idea. I just thought that it wasn't backed well. But rethinking of it I
 agree with you that "Talking about music is like dancing about
 architecture", so it can't be really explained. It's a matter of taste and
 imagination too, maybe. The only doubt I can think of is that haikus are
 very short, and Ozu's shots are generally very long - havenig a long-long
 "breath", so they seem not to have the same tempo. But again, I appologize
